          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD",
                "HE3SP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detection system SFiNx consists of",
                "box-like assembly of double-sided silicon",
                "strip detectors ( DSSD )surrounded by 116 neutron",
                "counters filled with He3 at 7 atm pressure.",
                "Single neutron detection efficiency calibration was",
                "carried out using the 248Cm source, assuming that",
                "the energy spectrum of prompt SF neutrons of 250No does",
                "not differ significantly from that of 248Cm.",
                "The single neutron detection efficiency (56+-1) %.",
                "The DSSD placed at the focal plane of SHELS consisted",
                "of 128 x 128 strips, its area was 100 x 100 mm2.",
                "Eight side 16 x 16 DSSDs of 50 x 50 mm2 were located",
                "around the focal plane DSSD in the backward direction.",
                "DSSD energy calibration at alpha-particle energies was",
                "performed using the 174Yb(48Ca,xn)222-xTh reaction.",
                "Dead time of detection system 4.5 microsec."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " 1357 events of 252No spontaneous fission were found."
              ]
            }
          ],
